    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-12-09T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-12-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="500"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d500">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10657: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-09T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 9, 1929—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:21 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1112. Legation’s 1107, December 8, 4 p.m. Commander in chief telegraphed December
                    8th that he will leave Manila for Shanghai December<note n="1" xml:id="d500fn1"
                        >The Curtiss Aeroplane Export Corporation, Garden City, L. I., and New York,
                        and the Aviation Exploration, Inc. (Del.), New York.</note> 11th and that,
                    until present confused political conditions are clarified, a division of
                    destroyers, less those undergoing overhaul, will be assigned to Chinese ports.
                    Destroyers leave Manila December 9th.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
